 The bulls maintained their grip on the market activities, as stocks sustained rally for the fourth trading session following gains recorded majorly by blue chip stocks.
The key market performance measures, the NSE All Share Index and market capitalisation, rose by 0.15 per cent, as market sentiments extended gaining streaks following investors’ sustained optimism.
Consequently, the All-Share Index gained 48.23 basis points or 0.15 per cent to close at 30,821.80 as against 30,773.57 recorded the previous day, while the market capitalisation of equities appreciated by N18 billion or 0.15 per cent to close at N11.493 trillion from N11.475 trillion, as market sentiment remained on the green zone. Meanwhile, a turnover of 369 million shares exchanged in 3,319 deals was recorded in the day’s trading.
Premium sub-sector was the most active (measured by turnover volume) with 169.7 million shares exchanged by investors in 1,074 deals.
Volume in the sub-sector was largely driven by activities in the shares of Access Bank Plc and Zenith Bank Plc.
Banking sub-sector boosted by activities in the shares of GTB Plc and ETI Plc trailed with a turnover of 63 million shares in 723 deals. The number of gainers at the close of trading session was 19, while decliners closed at 17.
Learn Africa Plc led the gainers’ table with a gain of 9.49 per cent to close at N1.50 per share, while Regency Insurance Plc tailed with a gain of 9.09 per cent to close at 24 kobo per share. MC Nichols Plc added 9.69 per cent to close at 42 kobo per share.
On the other hand, Custodian Investment Plc led the price losers’ table, dropping 8.82 per cent to close at N6.20 per share. Guinea Insurance Plc followed with 8.70 per cent to close at 21 kobo per share while CHI Plc trailed with a loss of 6.45 per cent to close at 29 kobo per share.